The thermostat controls the AC unit's operation based on temperature settings.

The indoor unit contains the air filter, which must be cleaned or replaced for proper function.

component,cooling process
The outdoor unit uses refrigerant to cool, and leaks can cause operational issues.

component failure,operation
A faulty capacitor can prevent the AC unit from turning on or functioning correctly.

component,power supply
The transformer provides power to components of the indoor unit, and its failure can cause operational issues.

data.tgt_id: Issue 1: AC Unit is Not Cooling
data.content:
Air Filter	Issue 1: AC Unit is Not Cooling
maintenance,troubleshooting
Checking and cleaning or replacing the air filter is a step in troubleshooting the issue of the AC unit not cooling.

data.src_id: Issue 2: AC Unit Will Not Turn On
data.content:
Issue 2: AC Unit Will Not Turn On	Thermostat
control,operation
The thermostat's setting and operation are crucial in determining why the AC unit will not turn on.

data.tgt_id: Issue 3: AC is Making a Loud Noise
data.content:
Capacitor	Issue 3: AC is Making a Loud Noise
component failure,noise
A faulty capacitor could be the cause of loud noises from the AC unit, as it affects the unit's operation.

AC Unit	Circuit Breaker
operation,safety
The circuit breaker can prevent the AC unit from operating if it trips due to an electrical issue.

Disconnect Switch	Outdoor Unit (Condenser)
component,power control
The disconnect switch controls power supply to the outdoor unit and is crucial for its operation.

Disconnect Switch	Fuses
component failure,safety
Fuses within the disconnect switch can blow and prevent the AC unit from operating if there's an electrical issue.

AC Unit	Transformer
component relationship,power supply
The transformer is a component of the AC unit, providing power to the system.

Condenser Fan	Fan Motor
mechanical relationship,noise cause
The fan motor drives the condenser fan, and if worn out, can cause noise.

AC Unit	Blower Wheel
component relationship,system performance
The blower wheel is part of the indoor unit of the AC system, and issues with it can affect overall performance.

AC Unit	Refrigerant Lines
noise cause,system relationship
The refrigerant lines are essential for the AC system's operation, and if loose or vibrating, can cause noise.

Electrician	Troubleshooting Guide
knowledge application,user relationship
The electrician uses the troubleshooting guide to identify and fix issues with the AC unit.

The outdoor unit is a part of the AC system, housing critical components such as the condenser fan.

AC Unit	Indoor Unit
component relationship,system structure

Condenser Fan	Debris
